{"ts":"2026-07-13T14:23:57.531Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-chyh"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"GH-544: linked-file path anchoring — files/docs add/glob/discover/validate-paths resolve at process.cwd() while validate --check-files anchors at the workspace root"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"From a monorepo subdirectory, pm files/docs --add, --add-glob, --discover, and --validate-paths anchor relative paths at process.cwd() (src/sdk/files.ts runFilesDiscover; src/sdk/linked-artifacts.ts:350 expandAddGlobEntries cwd, :448 validateLinkedPaths), while pm validate --check-files classifies against resolveWorkspaceRoot(pmRoot) (src/cli/commands/validate.ts:725, :3356). resolvePmRoot walks up ancestors, so subdirectory invocations succeed but store paths that validate later reports as missing — silent files_missing drift, invisible at write time because --validate-paths shares the cwd anchor. Promoted to public SDK surface by PR#543, so external consumers now inherit the cwd dependence. Fix direction: single workspace-root anchoring contract across write and check sides; re-anchor cwd-relative input at store time. Class precedent pm-og1v (closed, lancedb store path). See GH-544."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["cli","data-integrity","files","sdk"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-13T14:23:57.531Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-13T14:23:57.531Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":120},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"All linked-path resolution surfaces (files/docs --add, --add-glob expansion, --discover containment, --validate-paths probing) anchor stored paths at resolveWorkspaceRoot(pmRoot), not process.cwd(); relative CLI input is interpreted against cwd then re-anchored to the workspace root before storage; a subdirectory-cwd regression test proves pm files --add + pm validate --check-files agree; SDK docs for runFiles/runFilesDiscover/validateLinkedPaths state the workspace-root anchoring contract"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-33cw"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"18bf30c61e1b003b8646f00a42e6deaf213a921779a17b174a444bb23bca1c6e","message":""}
